---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHero from "../components/PageHero.astro";

const updated = "May 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms — fwd."
  description="The short, honest version of our terms of service. What you get, what we ask, and what's not included."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow={`Last updated · ${updated}`}
    title="The short, <em>honest version</em> of our terms."
    lede="A plain-language summary of how we work together. For larger projects we'll send a proper SOW; for Landing and Full Site this is the working agreement."
  />

  <section class="pb-24">
    <div class="container-page prose-page reveal">
      <h2>1 · What you get</h2>
      <p>
        The deliverable described on
        <a href="/services">our services page</a>
        — a Landing Page or Full Site — built around your brand, with hosting
        setup, domain connection, and the agreed number of revision rounds.
      </p>

      <h2>2 · What we need from you</h2>
      <p>
        Content (text, photos, logos), timely feedback during revision rounds,
        and a working point of contact who can make decisions. We can help
        with copy direction but cannot write your business positioning for
        you from scratch.
      </p>

      <h2>3 · Timelines</h2>
      <p>
        Landing pages typically ship in one to two weeks; Full Sites in two
        to four. Timelines assume responsive feedback. If we don't hear from
        you for more than three weeks, the project may pause and resume at
        our next available slot.
      </p>

      <h2>4 · Payment</h2>
      <p>
        50% to begin, 50% on launch. We invoice via Stripe or bank transfer.
        Prices on the services page are flat — no hidden line items.
      </p>

      <h2>5 · Ownership</h2>
      <p>
        Once final payment is received, all design and code we produce for
        your project is yours. We retain the right to show the work in our
        portfolio unless you specifically ask us not to.
      </p>

      <h2>6 · Hosting &amp; domain</h2>
      <p>
        We set up hosting and a domain connection at launch. You pay the
        providers directly (typically $5–$20/month and ~$15/year respectively)
        — we don't mark these up. You can move the site off our recommended
        host at any time.
      </p>

      <h2>7 · Revisions</h2>
      <p>
        Landing includes one revision round; Full Site includes two. A
        revision round means a consolidated set of changes returned together,
        not a stream of one-off requests. Out-of-scope work is quoted
        separately and honestly.
      </p>

      <h2>8 · Not included</h2>
      <p>
        Logo design, copywriting from scratch, ongoing maintenance retainers,
        e-commerce, and custom integrations are not part of the standard
        tiers. We'll happily quote any of these as add-ons.
      </p>

      <h2>9 · Cancellation</h2>
      <p>
        If you decide not to proceed after kickoff, the 50% deposit is
        non-refundable — it covers the design and research time already
        invested. If we cancel for any reason on our end, you get a full
        refund and any files we've produced.
      </p>

      <h2>10 · Questions</h2>
      <p>
        Anything unclear? Email
        <a href="mailto:hello@fwd.studio">hello@fwd.studio</a>
        — we'll answer in plain English.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose-page {
    max-width: 65ch;
    margin-inline: auto;
    color: var(--color-fg-soft);
    font-size: var(--text-step-0);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .prose-page h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: var(--text-step-2);
    color: var(--color-fg);
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    margin: 2.5rem 0 0.75rem;
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 80, "SOFT" 30;
  }
  .prose-page p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }
  .prose-page a {
    color: var(--color-blue);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-line);
  }
  .prose-page a:hover { border-bottom-color: var(--color-blue); }
</style>
